Title:
Unauthorized Access to Payroll Group Management by External Users

Description:
An external user, lacking permissions on the payroll group, is able to view, modify, and add new payroll groups. This access exposes sensitive payroll information and enables unauthorized modifications, potentially leading to data manipulation or misuse.

Recommendation:
Implement strict access controls to verify that only authorized users with proper permissions can view or modify payroll group data. This includes applying role-based access controls (RBAC) for payroll management and conducting periodic access reviews to ensure permissions are correctly assigned. Additionally, implement auditing mechanisms to detect unauthorized access attempts.


